answers.body_markdown:
I have found a solution. It&#39;s not the most elegant, but I finally decided to use `setInterval()` &amp; make an **new API call** every **10 seconds**. Getting fresh data every **10 seconds** won&#39;t reach the **[Stack Exchange API&#39;s daily limit](https://api.stackexchange.com/docs/throttle)** &amp; solves my problem.

**Code Snippet:**

```
&lt;script&gt;
import axios from &#39;axios&#39;

export default {
  name: &#39;QuestionInfo&#39;,
  data(){
    return {
      details: [],
      tag: `jquery`,
      newTag: &#39;&#39;
    }
  },
  // makes an API call on page load
  mounted() {
    this.getTag()
  },
  methods: {
    getTag(){
      setInterval(() =&gt; {
        axios.get(`https://api.stackexchange.com//2.2/questions?order=desc&amp;sort=creation&amp;tagged=${this.tag}&amp;site=stackoverflow`).then(response =&gt; {
          this.details = response.data.items[0]
        // console.log an error if get() method is unsuccessful
        }).catch(err =&gt; {
          console.log(err)
        })
      }, 10000);
    },
    updateTag() {
      this.tag = this.newTag
      this.getTag();
    },
  },
}
&lt;/script&gt;
```

